# ============================================================================
# Mirava Magic Prompt - Environment Variables
# ============================================================================
#
# ⚠️  IMPORTANT: Environment variables are NO LONGER exposed to the client!
#
# This application uses Cloudflare Pages Functions to keep credentials
# server-side. Set these variables in the Cloudflare Pages dashboard:
#
# Cloudflare Dashboard > Pages > Your Project > Settings > Environment Variables
#
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# Cloudflare Pages Environment Variables (Set in Dashboard)
# ============================================================================
#
# SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key-here
#
# ⚠️  NOTE: Use SERVICE_ROLE_KEY (not anon key) for server-side operations.
#     This key has full access and should NEVER be exposed to clients.
#
# Get these from: Supabase Dashboard > Project Settings > API
#
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# Local Development (.env file)
# ============================================================================
#
# For local development, the app runs in DEMO MODE automatically.
# No Supabase connection is needed for development.
#
# Demo mode features:
# - Stats stored in localStorage
# - Cross-tab sync via BroadcastChannel
# - Full functionality without backend
#
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# LEGACY (No Longer Used - Kept for Reference)
# ============================================================================
# 
# Previously, VITE_ prefixed variables were used:
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
#
# These are NO LONGER USED and should be removed if present.
# The new architecture keeps all credentials server-side.
#
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# Security Architecture
# ============================================================================
#
#                    CLIENT (Browser)
#                         │
#                         │ HTTPS
#                         ▼
#              ┌──────────────────────┐
#              │ Cloudflare Pages     │
#              │ Edge Functions       │
#              │ (/api/stats)         │
#              │                      │
#              │ [Credentials Here]   │
#              └──────────────────────┘
#                         │
#                         │ HTTPS
#                         ▼
#              ┌──────────────────────┐
#              │ Supabase             │
#              │ (Database + RLS)     │
#              └──────────────────────┘
#
# Benefits:
# ✅ No credentials in client bundle
# ✅ No credentials visible in DevTools
# ✅ Service role key enables RPC calls
# ✅ Edge functions run close to users
# ✅ Cloudflare handles rate limiting
#
# ============================================================================
